      <section id="details">
        <h2 class="gem-c-heading gem-c-heading--font-size-27 gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Details</h2>


        
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>This research examined awareness and understanding of Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme amongst employees and employers and employersâ€™ experiences of applying to the scheme.</p>

<p>The research included two survey waves with employers, with wave 1 fieldwork completed before the Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme opened for applications on 20 April 2020, and wave 2 fieldwork taking place after applications had opened.</p>

<p>The findings from the wave 1 survey on awareness and understanding of Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme were used by <abbr title="HM Revenue and Customs">HMRC</abbr> to support communications strategy and implementation.</p>

<p>The findings from the wave 2 survey were used by <abbr title="HM Revenue and Customs">HMRC</abbr> to understand the overall experience of customers applying for the Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme, and awareness of changes to the scheme.</p>

<p>One survey with employees was also conducted. The research aimed to help <abbr title="HM Revenue and Customs">HMRC</abbr> understand employee perceptions and knowledge of the Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme, before it opened</p>

<p>Findings should be treated as indicative due to the sampling methodology possible in the time available.</p>

</div>
</div>

